        <h2>1. BuildingConnected — Best for GC bid solicitation</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> ~$5,000–$10,000+/yr for GCs; free for subcontractors to receive invitations</p>

        <p>BuildingConnected (now owned by Autodesk) has become the dominant platform for commercial GCs managing subcontractor bid solicitation. When you put a project out to bid, you build an invitation list from BuildingConnected's massive subcontractor network, send ITBs with plan sets attached, track responses, and level the bids you receive — all in one system.</p>

        <p><strong>Why GCs choose BuildingConnected:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Subcontractor database is enormous — most commercial subs in your market are already in the system</li>
          <li>Bid leveling tool compares sub bids across scope items side by side</li>
          <li>Tracks which subs opened your ITB, declined, or are working on a bid</li>
          <li>Integrates with Autodesk Build for seamless pre-construction to project handoff</li>
          <li>Stores historical sub performance data for smarter future invitations</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Expensive for GCs — pricing reflects its dominance in the market</li>
          <li>Subcontractors increasingly feel spammed by ITBs on projects outside their capacity or geography</li>
          <li>Bid leveling tool is good but requires subs to follow your provided scope structure</li>
        </ul>

